<DOC><DOCNO> AP900314-0096 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-14-90 1404EST</FILEID><FIRST>u w PM-Bush-Thatcher 2ndLd-Writethru a0622 03-14 0316</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bush-Thatcher, 2nd Ld-Writethru, a0622,280</SECOND><HEAD>Bush to Meet with Thatcher, Mitterrand</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: New throughout to include Mitterrand meeting</NOTE><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Bush will meet separately next monthwith British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher and French PresidentFrancois Mitterrand to discuss issues facing NATO, the White Houseannounced today.   Bush will meet with Mrs. Thatacher in Bermuda on April 13 andwith Mitterrand in Florida on April 19.   ``As the year unfolds, the president will continue to consultclosely with his counterparts in the Atlantic community on thehistoric changes in Europe,'' presidential spokesman MarlinFitzwater said in a statement.   After Bush and Mrs. Thatcher hold their informal meeting in theBritish colony, the president will spend the night on the island,returning to Washington on April 14.   Bush met with Mrs. Thatcher in London last year and again in1989 when she visited him at Camp David, the presidential retreatin Maryland's Catoctin Mountains.   ``The president and the prime minister will discuss a wide rangeof issues related to events in Eastern Europe, NATO and bilateralrelations,'' a White House statement said.   In London, a spokeswoman for Mrs. Thatcher said she was due tomeet Bush in July but the April meeting was set up ``by mutualagreement because of the pace of world events.''   Mrs. Thatcher will spend two nights on the island, aself-governing British colony, the spokeswoman added, speaking oncondition of anonymity.   Mitterrand and Bush met last December on the French Carribbeanisland of St. Martin. The president also invited Mitterrand to hisoceanside home in Kennebunkport, Maine, last May and the two metduring last July's seven-nation economic summit in Paris.   White House aides said the session with Mitterrand would takeplace in South Florida, but an exact location has not yet beendetrmined. Bush had been scheduled to be in Islamorada, in theFlorida Keys, on April 20.</TEXT></DOC>